MPUMALANGA police have launched a manhunt for suspects after two taxi owners were targeted at Barberton outside Mbombela on Friday evening, 12 February. Brigadier Leonard Hlathi said: “A taxi owner (34) parked his Toyota Quantum at the house of a certain motor mechanic and alighted. An armed man emerged out of nowhere. The gun-wielding man fired a shot aimed at the victim, and then fled the scene.” He said paramedics were notified but upon arrival, the victim was unfortunately certified dead,” Hlathi added. “The motive for the killing is unknown. However, police are requesting Andries Mdluli, whom they believe can be of assistance in this investigation, to contact the investigation officer urgently, or anyone who may know about his whereabouts to contact the police. A case of murder was opened.” Meanwhile, a similar incident occurred in Barberton on Thursday, 11 February. A taxi owner’s family came under attack when suspects opened fire at his house. Fortunately, no one was injured. “Police were informed about this incident and a case of attempted murder was opened. Preliminary investigation suggests that the suspects were targeting the taxi owner who was not home at the time,” said Hlathi. Police urge anyone with information to call Captain Jabulani Mashiane on 082 373 9097, Crime Stop at 08600 10111 or send information via MYSAPSAPP.